{
  "texts": [
    "The benefit of using a nonuniform grid is twofold.",
    "First, it allows using a smaller number of grid points as compared to the corresponding uniform grid covering the same computational domain.",
    "Secondly, depending on the particular setup, the computational time step can be noticeably larger than the one from the uniform grid.",
    "For example, if we consider a nonmagnetic subsonic flow, the time step is limited by the sound speed, c S, which varies along the z-direction.",
    "In the case of the uniform grid the time step is proportional to t ∝ z/c S,max, where c S,max corresponds to the highest sound speed from the hot corona region, and it limits the time step in the whole domain."
  ]
}